---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";

export const prerender = true;

const lastUpdated = "April 2, 2026";
---

<Layout
  title="Privacy Policy — Visupair"
  description="How Visupair collects, uses, and protects your personal data when you use visupair.com."
>
  <div class="account-page">
    <div class="legal-island">
      <article class="legal-page">
        <header class="legal-header">
          <p class="legal-kicker">Legal</p>
          <h1 class="legal-title">Privacy Policy</h1>
          <p class="legal-meta">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>
        </header>

        <div class="legal-body">
          <p>
            This Privacy Policy explains how <strong>Visupair</strong> handles personal data when you visit
            <a href="https://visupair.com">visupair.com</a>, create an account,
            buy products or services, or contact Visupair. It is meant to be readable.
            If anything is unclear, email
            <a href="mailto:info@visupair.com">info@visupair.com</a>.
          </p>
          <p>
            For the rules of using the site, see the
            <a href="/legal/terms-of-service">Terms of Service</a>. For cookies,
            see the <a href="/legal/cookie-policy">Cookie Policy</a>.
          </p>

          <h2>1. Who is responsible</h2>
          <p>
            The <strong>data controller</strong> for personal data described
            here is Visupair, operating the website at visupair.com. If required
            by law in your market, Visupair will publish or provide the legal name and
            postal address of the seller on request or on the site (for example
            in an imprint or checkout information).
          </p>

          <h2>2. What data Visupair collects</h2>
          <p>Depending on what you do on the site, Visupair may process:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>
              <strong>Account and profile</strong> — email address, name (if
              you provide it), profile image (for example from social sign-in),
              password <em>hash</em> if you use email/password (Visupair does not store
              your password in plain text), and account preferences linked to
              your profile.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Orders and fulfilment</strong> — shipping name and address,
              contact details, order contents, payment status, and related
              messages needed to deliver physical goods or grant access to
              digital goods.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Payment data</strong> — payments are handled by Visupair’s
              payment provider. Visupair typically receives limited information (for
              example last digits of a card or payment confirmation, customer
              identifiers, and fraud signals); Visupair does <strong>not</strong> store
              your full card number on its own servers.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Communications</strong> — messages you send to Visupair (support,
              contact forms, service requests) and transactional emails Visupair sends
              you (verification, password resets, order updates where
              applicable).
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Technical and usage data</strong> — IP address, device and
              browser type, approximate location derived from IP, pages viewed,
              and similar data from logs and security tools. This helps Visupair run,
              secure, and improve the site.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Favourites and in-app activity</strong> — for example
              product IDs you save while logged in.
            </li>
          </ul>

          <h2>3. Why Visupair uses your data and legal bases (GDPR)</h2>
          <p>
            Where EU/EEA/UK data protection law applies, Visupair relies on the
            following <strong>legal bases</strong>:
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>
              <strong>Contract</strong> — processing needed to provide the site,
              your account, checkout, delivery, downloads, and paid services you
              request.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Legitimate interests</strong> — for example securing the
              site, preventing fraud and abuse, improving performance, measuring
              aggregate use in a privacy-respecting way, and contacting you about
              your account or orders where not strictly contractual.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Consent</strong> — where required for optional cookies or
              marketing (see the
              <a href="/legal/cookie-policy">Cookie Policy</a>). You may
              withdraw consent at any time where Visupair relies on it.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Legal obligation</strong> — for example tax, accounting, or
              responding to lawful requests from authorities.
            </li>
          </ul>

          <h2>4. Who Visupair shares data with</h2>
          <p>
            Visupair uses carefully selected <strong>service providers</strong>
            (“processors”) who process data on Visupair’s instructions and under
            appropriate agreements:
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>
              <strong>Cloudflare, Inc.</strong> — website hosting, content
              delivery, security, and related infrastructure (traffic and log
              data may be processed when you use the site).
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Stripe, Inc.</strong> (and affiliates as applicable) —
              payment processing and fraud prevention when you pay.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Google LLC</strong> — if you choose
              <strong>Sign in with Google</strong>, Google processes data needed
              for authentication under Google’s policies as well as Visupair’s.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Resend, Inc.</strong> — sending transactional email (for
              example email verification and password reset).
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Sanity AS</strong> — Visupair’s content platform for publishing
              products, portfolio, and related website content. It may process
              technical data when the site loads content from Sanity’s services.
            </li>
          </ul>
          <p>
            Visupair may also share information when required by law, to protect
            rights and safety, or in connection with a merger or asset transfer
            (with notice where appropriate).
          </p>

          <h2>5. Transfers outside your country</h2>
          <p>
            Some providers listed above are based in the United States or other
            countries outside the EEA/UK. Where personal data is transferred, Visupair
            relies on tools recognised by EU/UK law (for example
            <strong>Standard Contractual Clauses</strong> or provider mechanisms
            offered under those frameworks), unless another valid transfer tool
            applies.
          </p>

          <h2>6. How long Visupair keeps data</h2>
          <p>
            Visupair keeps personal data only as long as needed for the purposes above,
            including legal, tax, and accounting obligations. Examples:
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>
              <strong>Account data</strong> — while your account is open and for
              a reasonable period after closure to resolve disputes or enforce
              terms, unless a longer period is required by law.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Order and invoice records</strong> — often several years
              where required for taxation and consumer rules.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Security logs</strong> — for a limited retention period
              appropriate to detect abuse and protect systems.
            </li>
          </ul>

          <h2>7. Your rights</h2>
          <p>
            Depending on where you live, you may have rights regarding your
            personal data, including to <strong>access</strong>, correct,
            delete, restrict, or <strong>port</strong> your data, to
            <strong>object</strong> to certain processing, and to withdraw
            consent where Visupair relies on it. You may also lodge a complaint with a
            data protection authority; in Poland this is commonly the
            <strong>PUODO</strong> (President of the Personal Data Protection
            Office), and in other countries your local supervisory authority.
          </p>
          <p>
            To exercise your rights, contact
            <a href="mailto:info@visupair.com">info@visupair.com</a>. Visupair may need
            to verify your identity before acting on a request.
          </p>

          <h2>8. Security</h2>
          <p>
            Visupair uses industry-standard measures suited to the nature of Visupair’s
            service (for example encryption in transit, access controls, and
            secure hosting). No method of transmission over the internet is
            perfectly secure; Visupair works to reduce risk and respond to issues
            responsibly.
          </p>

          <h2>9. Children</h2>
          <p>
            The Visupair site is not directed at children under 16 (or the age required
            in your country). Visupair does not knowingly collect children’s personal
            data for marketing. If you believe Visupair has collected such data, email
            <a href="mailto:info@visupair.com">info@visupair.com</a> and Visupair will take appropriate steps to delete it.
          </p>

          <h2>10. Changes</h2>
          <p>
            Visupair may update this Policy from time to time. The “Last updated” date
            at the top will change and, where the update is material, Visupair may also
            notify you on the site or by email if Visupair has your address.
          </p>

          <h2>11. Contact</h2>
          <p>
            Privacy questions:
            <a href="mailto:info@visupair.com">info@visupair.com</a>
          </p>
        </div>
      </article>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>

<style>
  /* Same shell as /legal/terms-of-service */
  .account-page {
    padding: 0 12px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .legal-island {
    background: var(--surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--border-subtle);
    border-radius: var(--radius-xl);
    min-height: calc(100vh - 420px);
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: stretch;
    padding: clamp(1.5rem, 3.5vw, 2.75rem) clamp(1.1rem, 3vw, 2.25rem);
  }

  .legal-page {
    width: 100%;
    max-width: min(90ch, 100%);
    margin-inline: auto;
    text-align: start;
    padding-block: 0.25rem 1rem;
    animation: legalFadeIn 0.45s ease-out;
    flex: 1;
  }

  @keyframes legalFadeIn {
    from {
      opacity: 0;
      transform: translateY(6px);
    }
    to {
      opacity: 1;
      transform: translateY(0);
    }
  }

  .legal-header {
    margin-bottom: 2.25rem;
    padding-bottom: 1.5rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-subtle);
    text-align: start;
  }

  .legal-kicker {
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.14em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    margin: 0 0 0.5rem;
  }

  .legal-title {
    font-size: clamp(1.75rem, 4vw, 2.25rem);
    font-weight: 600;
    margin: 0 0 0.5rem;
    line-height: 1.15;
  }

  .legal-meta {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    margin: 0;
  }

  .legal-body {
    font-size: clamp(1rem, 0.25vw + 0.96rem, 1.0625rem);
    line-height: 1.75;
    color: var(--text-secondary, var(--foreground));
    text-align: start;
    overflow-wrap: break-word;
  }

  .legal-body h2 {
    font-size: 1.08rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    margin: 2.25rem 0 0.65rem;
    line-height: 1.35;
    color: var(--foreground);
  }

  .legal-body p {
    margin: 0 0 1.1rem;
  }

  .legal-body ul {
    margin: 0.25rem 0 1.25rem;
    padding-inline-start: 1.35rem;
    list-style-position: outside;
  }

  .legal-body li {
    margin: 0 0 0.55rem;
    padding-inline-start: 0.2rem;
  }

  .legal-body li:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .legal-body a {
    color: var(--accent, #a78bfa);
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 2px;
  }

  .legal-body a:hover {
    opacity: 0.9;
  }
</style>
